modules.description: Handles conversion and validation of IP addresses between string and binary formats, with support for both IPv4 and IPv6. Manages MAC address parsing, formatting, and comparison operations. Validates input formats and ensures correct representation in network byte order.

Provides functions to evaluate and print MAC address expressions, working with strings and formatatters. Processes input strings to validate and display MAC addresses, supporting custom printer configurations. Enables interactive evaluation of MAC address literals in a REPL environment.

Extracts and constructs MAC addresses from byte sequences or string representations, converting between binary and human-readable formats. Provides operations to check address properties like unicast or local administration, and to retrieve the OUI identifier. Outputs formatted strings with customizable separators and supports comparison for ordering.
